# Installing miniconda 

Download miniconda package and install it 
Check the minicona path: /Users/Desktop/miniconda3  (Use yours)

Permanently add Miniconda to PATH:

Add this line to your shell configuration file (so it works every time you open a new terminal):

For bash users, edit ~/.bashrc (or ~/.bash_profile on macOS Terminal).

For zsh users, edit ~/.zshrc.

Add this line at the end: export PATH="/Users/alakh/Desktop/miniconda3/bin:$PATH"

use terminal: source ~/.bashrc (or zshrc)
check: conda --version

Use conda now

conda create -n marbl-env python=3.11
conda activate marbl-env
conda install doxygen graphviz
conda install mamba -c conda-forge
